FT  16 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Firstland requests suspension at 7p
Shares of Firstland Group, formerly Firstland Oil &amp; Gas, were suspended
yesterday at 7p at the company's request pending shareholders' approval of
reorganisation proposals.
The company, which intends to diversify away from its oil and gas interests,
said terms had been agreed for the acquisition of a private packaging
company substantially larger than Firstland, for about Pounds 4.8m.
The company's shares trade on the USM.
